1
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:55,740
=Sugar and Lies=
(A Different Her: The Women's Trilogy)

2
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:59,780
=Episode 2=
=Let's Elope Now=

3
00:01:15,250 --> 00:01:18,570
♪Everything in my memories
feels so beautiful♪

4
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,800
Have you made up your mind?

5
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:26,620
♪In every photo,
your smiles are always so bright♪

6
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,960
Didn't we agree you'd make it up to me?

7
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:39,750
♪Giving off a laid-back vibe♪

8
00:02:08,610 --> 00:02:15,390
♪Maybe time will slowly wear our edges down♪

9
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:22,110
♪When we look back,
we'll just laugh at our youth♪

10
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:29,070
♪If we could go back,
even for a second♪

11
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:36,590
♪I'd give up everything
just to see your smile again♪

12
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,960
(Is this)

13
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,080
(a dream?)

14
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,320
After all these years,

15
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,580
you're still using the same wallpaper.

16
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,480
Were you looking in my phone?

17
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,040
Not interested.

18
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,720
Your phone kept ringing last night.

19
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,360
So I put it on silent for you.

20
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,000
Move aside.

21
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,840
I'm heading out.

22
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,320
How was my service last night?

23
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:16,800
Honestly,

24
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,080
it was just okay.

25
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,960
Then let's do it again.

26
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:40,820
(Keep Love)

27
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,600
Ruomai.

28
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,040
Where's Ding Daang?

29
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,720
President Hu.

30
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,320
Sorry about that.

31
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:56,240
She had too much to drink last night.

32
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,840
I took her back to my place.

33
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,560
Then take me to your place.

34
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,880
She left early this morning.

35
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,400
Said she was heading
to the temple to pray.

36
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:06,920
The temple?

37
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,120
Which temple?

38
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,560
That temple on Mount Nan.

39
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,200
She said years ago,

40
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,800
she made a wish there

41
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,080
for a good marriage.

42
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:17,920
Isn't it a tradition to repay the wish
once it comes true?

43
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,160
But why didn't she answer my phone?

44
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:26,560
Maybe she's busying praying
at the temple.

45
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,760
President Hu, please don't worry.

46
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,440
She'll be back soon.

47
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,240
I'm really anxious
that we can't find her.

48
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,080
Don't panic.

49
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,800
You have to trust me.

50
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,640
No,

51
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,160
trust Ding Daang.

52
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:55,220
(Keep Love)

53
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,080
Baby,

54
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,160
- if...
- I choose you.

55
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,880
- What if...
- Still you.

56
00:06:00,370 --> 00:06:01,240
But if...

57
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,080
You're my priority.

58
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,640
I haven't yet...

59
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,520
You're the most beautiful woman
in the world.

60
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,760
- I...
- Buy what you like.

61
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:10,300
I'll go with whatever you say.

62
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,960
Baby, you're just too sweet.

63
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,720
With Keep Love around,

64
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,040
no more arguing.

65
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,440
But endless sweetness.

66
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,840
Keep Love just got

67
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:19,840
two brand-new features.

68
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,240
One's the Quarrel Shield,

69
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,520
which helps couples work through

70
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,800
any kind of disagreement,

71
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,080
big or small.

72
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,480
The other is the Pain Barrier,

73
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,080
turning every heartbreak

74
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,800
into a warm memory.

75
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,160
I told you, I really can't pay it back.

76
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,640
If you truly want to help me,

77
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,880
please keep your distance.

78
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,080
Aming.

79
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,200
I've made up my mind.

80
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,540
I'm studying abroad with Professor Luo.

81
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,040
Chen Aming.

82
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,240
I'm going to make you pay for this.

83
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,040
Ding Daang doesn't need you

84
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,800
to keep going with life.

85
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,400
With Keep Love around,

86
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,200
no matter how many years pass,

87
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,320
no matter the misunderstandings between you,

88
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,720
your first love

89
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:59,080
will still be the one you hold dearly.

90
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:02,400
Congratulations!

91
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,800
You had excellent sleep last night.

92
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,200
Everything's on track so far.

93
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,800
If you truly feel guilty about
what happened,

94
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,280
stay with me for one more week.

95
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,640
So, what do you say?

96
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,280
Have you made up your mind?

97
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,160
Since you made that choice back then,

98
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,800
you shouldn't have come back.

99
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,800
Why show up all of a sudden?

100
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,640
Why come back just to mess with my life?

101
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,400
Ding,

102
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,840
I don't care where you are.

103
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,880
Get back here right now.

104
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:48,720
Now!

105
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:50,600
Ruomai.

106
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,960
Hey, don't panic, okay?

107
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,920
How can I not panic?

108
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,520
So 'singles' night' means
not coming home all night?

109
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:58,880
You know,

110
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,920
I've been waiting for him for so long.

111
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:03,680
I just want to spend
a few more days with him.

112
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,680
Do you even realize what you're saying?

113
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,760
Don't you see how risky that is?

114
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,960
Ruomai.

115
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,320
You know best about me.

116
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,040
Alright, alright, I get it.

117
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,880
But let's be clear first.

118
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,280
Take good care of yourself.

119
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,000
Don't let yourself fall for him again.

120
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,520
If anything happens,

121
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:23,080
tell me right away.

122
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,480
Give me a little more time.

123
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,880
I'll think it through carefully.

124
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:28,960
Hey!

125
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,190
Were you eavesdropping?

126
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,600
Have you figured out

127
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,440
how to explain it to your fiancé?

128
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,720
What is it?

129
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:09,840
You getting scared?

130
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,360
Like it or not,

131
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,480
you've already become

132
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,840
the third wheel.

133
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,800
I'm just starting out in Mancheng.

134
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,040
Getting tangled in your relationship,

135
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,880
isn't going to do me any good.

136
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,840
If you truly cared,

137
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,400
nothing wouldn't have happened.

138
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,920
But since it already did,

139
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,640
the fallout

140
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,240
is yours to deal with.

141
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,320
So, Miss Ding, you'd already set me up.

142
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,680
Alright then.

143
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,000
Miss Ding,

144
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,600
what's your plan for today?

145
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,720
I'm in, all the way.

146
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,600
You ordered takeout from my shop.

147
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,280
What's your intention here?

148
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,040
The daily limited chestnut cake.

149
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,520
Top seller in the whole store.

150
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,400
I've just got to taste it.

151
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,120
Do you need me to feed you?

152
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,050
Or you eat it yourself?

153
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,040
Tastes just like back then.

154
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,360
I'm warning you.

155
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,640
Don't act recklessly.

156
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:05,960
As long as you play nice,

157
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:09,040
I've got your back in Mancheng.

158
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:10,200
Otherwise...

159
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,480
Otherwise I'll get nowhere?

160
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,680
That could work.

161
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:18,880
Suga Love.

162
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,720
(Suga Love)
A lovely name.

163
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,720
I picked it at random.

164
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,480
Want me to help you pick a name?

165
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,120
I brought you a gift.

166
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:35,240
(Suga Love)
From your favorite author.

167
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,440
She's released a new book.

168
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,680
Where did you get it?

169
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:41,880
I picked it out for you

170
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,040
at the bookstore.

171
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:45,240
Funny thing.

172
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,920
The heroine's name is Ding Daang.

173
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,000
And the hero's

174
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,040
is called Aming.

175
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:52,560
Seriously?

176
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,440
What a coincidence.

177
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,640
I have to read it carefully.

178
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,440
On my way here,

179
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,360
I saw this delicious cake.

180
00:12:11,950 --> 00:12:13,120
I carried it all the way back

181
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,640
in case it's chipped. Try it.

182
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,600
Tastes good.

183
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:27,020
(Hu Yitong)

184
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,520
Ding Daang, you finally picked up.

185
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,200
Where have you been?

186
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,400
(Hu Yitong)
I bought breakfast for you.

187
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:39,960
She's already had one.

188
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,200
Who are you?

189
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:43,040
I'm her fiancé.

190
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,400
(Hu Yitong)
Then who am I?

191
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,560
Good question.

192
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,800
Call back when you figure that out.

193
00:13:59,060 --> 00:13:59,940
(Suga Love)

194
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,480
Is it fun?

195
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,480
Aren't you the one who likes a thrill?

196
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,840
Then let's play big.

197
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,560
So where exactly is Ding Daang now?

198
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:16,000
President Hu, please don't worry.

199
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,400
Before the engagement,

200
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,080
I promise I'll bring her to you.

201
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,400
The pain from one's family of origin

202
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:24,240
takes a lifetime to heal.

203
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,280
Gu Ruomai.

204
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,280
I'll be the one to heal her trauma.

205
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,680
We should get going.

206
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:29,840
Where to?

207
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:33,920
Let's elope.

208
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:06,060
♪I forgot this is a movie meant for one♪

209
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:17,820
♪Somehow you're still here,
crying with me♪

210
00:15:22,270 --> 00:15:24,210
♪They say♪

211
00:15:24,620 --> 00:15:33,000
♪Lovers should never hold hands
while watching a sad movie♪

212
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:36,500
♪Some endings cannot be changed♪

213
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:42,670
♪They don't belong in sweet memories♪

214
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:49,810
♪I've already lost you♪

215
00:15:49,810 --> 00:15:55,290
♪Thinking of it takes my breath away♪

216
00:15:55,590 --> 00:16:01,540
♪The movie ends, so many couples around♪

217
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:06,320
♪Yet none were ever like us♪

218
00:16:07,430 --> 00:16:11,460
♪The past will always pass♪

219
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:19,370
♪If you could still hold me tight
in your arms♪

220
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:23,090
♪I'd believe
that there are miracles in love♪

221
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:29,300
♪I'd prove
that I'm still in love with you♪

222
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:35,290
♪I've learned how to cherish
what we had♪

223
00:16:35,290 --> 00:16:41,550
♪But sadly, it's not you♪
